cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.RO 

This paper deals with vision-based autonomous driving and deep neural networks, which are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of gaze behavior also suggests a potential connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper involves training networks to mimic human behavior, which falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the application of the networks to autonomous driving suggests a connection to robotics (cs.RO).
